    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">A Certified ProAdvisor fixes the setup and reconciles the liabilities.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Updating a tax table is the easy part. The work that actually makes the numbers trustworthy is everything behind them: verifying each employee&rsquo;s filing status, allowances, exemptions, and work location; confirming the company and agency rates (including your current state SUI rate) and any mid-year change; setting up missing local or jurisdiction taxes; and reconciling the payroll liabilities report to what was actually withheld and paid, then correcting prior-period entries where they&rsquo;re wrong. A Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor with active Online and Desktop certifications does that against a written scope. We do not set the rates &mdash; the agencies do &mdash; and we do not file your payroll returns or give tax advice; filing and any notice or penalty stays with your CPA or EA (or Intuit&rsquo;s payroll e-file service if you run Intuit payroll). Independent firm &mdash; not Intuit, and not Intuit&rsquo;s software support.</p>
